@startuml
title Hình 5.13 - Bằng chứng resilience: Kafka outbox replay và Redis recovery

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam ArrowColor #475569
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.2
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #475569
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #F1F5F9
skinparam DatabaseBorderColor #475569
skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #DCFCE7
skinparam QueueBorderColor #475569
skinparam QueueBackgroundColor #FEF3C7

participant "Test script\nchaos scenario" as Test
participant "order-service" as Order #FEF3C7
database "order_db.outbox" as Outbox
queue "Kafka" as Kafka
participant "inventory-service" as Inventory
database "Redis" as Redis #FCE7F3
participant "product-service" as Product
participant "cart-service" as Cart
database ".test/results\nchaos transcripts" as Results

== Kill Kafka: Outbox replay ==
Test -> Kafka : stop container
Test -> Order : create order
Order -> Outbox : write event pending\nprocessed=false
Order --> Test : order accepted\nbusiness data persisted
Test -> Kafka : restart container
Order -> Outbox : OutboxPoller reads pending event
Order -> Kafka : replay event
Kafka -> Inventory : consume order-created
Inventory --> Order : inventory-updated
Order -> Outbox : mark processed
Test -> Results : record final state\norder CONFIRMED

== Kill Redis: degradation and recovery ==
Test -> Redis : stop container
Test -> Product : GET product list
Product --> Test : 200 fallback/no-cache path
Test -> Cart : cart operation
Cart --> Test : 500 fail fast\nRedis required
Test -> Redis : restart container
Test -> Cart : retry cart operation
Cart --> Test : recover 200
Test -> Results : record transcript

note bottom
  Outbox replay chứng minh hệ thống không mất event khi Kafka down.
  Redis scenario phân biệt luồng có fallback với luồng phải fail fast để tránh sai dữ liệu.
end note

@enduml
